{"title":"Engin Cycles’ dropper-friendly seat collar adds new size, stems drop prices","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/03/14/engin-cycles-has-some-exciting-new-products-on-the-horizon/","date":1615769347000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p>When Drew Guldalian of Engin Cycles says he’s been busy in the shop with projects for the last year, you know it’s going to be good.</p><p>A new, smaller 31.8 Seat Collar joins <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2019/05/22/eliminate-carbon-damage-and-dropper-binding-with-engin-cycles-seat-collar-now-aftermarket/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">their 34.9mm size</a> and should make many roadies, gravel cyclists, and 27.2mm seatpost lovers very happy.</p><p>The meticulous in-house machining promises a tight fit at low torque values, perfect for featherweight carbon fiber road bike frames and posts, or your enduro mountain bike with a finicky dropper post. The 31.8 Seat Collars come in four different anodized colors, your choice of titanium (17g, $52.00) or steel (18g, $45.00) bolts.</p><h3>Engin 35mm stems add steel bolt option</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/09003956/35MM-00666-0341601d6cab43b7eeb3d43e69a136f9.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/09003956/35MM-00666-0341601d6cab43b7eeb3d43e69a136f9.jpg\" alt=\"engin cycles 35mm mountain bike stems\" width=\"1000\" height=\"750\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/09003956/35MM-00666-0341601d6cab43b7eeb3d43e69a136f9.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/09003956/35MM-00666-0341601d6cab43b7eeb3d43e69a136f9.jpg 1000w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/09003956/35MM-00666-0341601d6cab43b7eeb3d43e69a136f9-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/09003956/35MM-00666-0341601d6cab43b7eeb3d43e69a136f9-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/09003956/35MM-00666-0341601d6cab43b7eeb3d43e69a136f9-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/09003956/35MM-00666-0341601d6cab43b7eeb3d43e69a136f9-768x576.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/09003956/35MM-00666-0341601d6cab43b7eeb3d43e69a136f9-696x522.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/09003956/35MM-00666-0341601d6cab43b7eeb3d43e69a136f9-560x420.jpg 560w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/09003956/35MM-00666-0341601d6cab43b7eeb3d43e69a136f9-80x60.jpg 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/09003956/35MM-00666-0341601d6cab43b7eeb3d43e69a136f9-265x198.jpg 265w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/09003956/35MM-00666-0341601d6cab43b7eeb3d43e69a136f9.jpg 1000w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/09003956/35MM-00666-0341601d6cab43b7eeb3d43e69a136f9-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/09003956/35MM-00666-0341601d6cab43b7eeb3d43e69a136f9-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/09003956/35MM-00666-0341601d6cab43b7eeb3d43e69a136f9-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/09003956/35MM-00666-0341601d6cab43b7eeb3d43e69a136f9-768x576.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/09003956/35MM-00666-0341601d6cab43b7eeb3d43e69a136f9-696x522.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/09003956/35MM-00666-0341601d6cab43b7eeb3d43e69a136f9-560x420.jpg 560w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/09003956/35MM-00666-0341601d6cab43b7eeb3d43e69a136f9-80x60.jpg 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/09003956/35MM-00666-0341601d6cab43b7eeb3d43e69a136f9-265x198.jpg 265w\"></a></p><p>For folks who love <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/08/28/engin-cycles-starts-offering-their-own-precision-mtb-stems-for-35mm-bars/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Engin’s 35mm MTB stem</a>, but didn’t have the cash to dish out (or care about saving a couple grams) will be pleased to hear you can get them in all the same colors, but now with steel hardware.&nbsp;That’ll save you $30, bringing the price down to $150 while only adding 7-8g.</p><h3>New framebuilding tools coming…</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/09003854/framejig-333b21acd0c803c9b19f19735cf93c75.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/09003854/framejig-333b21acd0c803c9b19f19735cf93c75.jpg\" alt=\"new bicycle framebuilding tools coming from drew guldalian\" width=\"640\" height=\"640\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/09003854/framejig-333b21acd0c803c9b19f19735cf93c75.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/